article.headline: Lipscomb 70, SIU-Edwardsville 47
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Adnan Hodzic scored 14 points and had 12 rebounds to lead Lipscomb to a 70-47 victory over Southern Illinois-Edwardsville on Tuesday night. Michael Lusk also scored 14 points for the Bisons (4-4), who held SIU-Edwardsville (2-8) scoreless for nearly eight minutes in the second half. Lipscomb led 29-25 before going on a 20-3 run to take a 49-28 advantage with 6:38 remaining in the game. Aaron Garriott's two free throws broke the Cougars' scoreless string that included 11 consecutive missed shots from the field. SIU-Edwardsville was 11 of 35 from the field (29.3 percent) for the game. Mark Yelovich scored 16 points and Barry Wellington added 11 points for the Cougars.
